Author::::leanmachine
DateTime::::2016-03-08T10:17:44Z
The resident Aussie Olympian whom I occassionally train with told me about a similar session that a friend of hers is doing in the lead-up to VLM. A/M: 25km steady pace runNo carbs whatsoever as part of the recovery, but unlimited proteinP/M: 4 x 1 mile reps as hard as possibleApparently it teaches the body to burn fat, which is what happens at the back end of a marathon when glycogen stores run out.



