Author::::David Chalfen
DateTime::::2016-03-08T09:37:32Z
Or if you are really keen and like Renato Canova more than having a nice sunday lunch, you can do this sort of thing whereby you run both the a/m and p/m legs at strong pace (details vary but not far short of MP, and at MP in parts) and - the grim marathon specific bit - going rather light on the carbs in between. Total volume on the day would be something like the longest of the long runs that you do. Mentally it's obvs a tough gig and physically it needs some planning to make it tough but not destructive.



